Note: Helper Functions - Cost Model
Note: ================================================================

Process called "estimate_execution_time_separate" that takes graph as Integer, node1 as Integer, node2 as Integer, cost_model as Integer returns Float:
    Note: Estimate execution time for separate kernels
    Note: time = compute_time + memory_time + 2 * launch_overhead

    Note: Estimate compute time (simplified: 1ms per operation)
    Let compute_time be 0.001 plus 0.001

    Note: Estimate memory time
    Let node1_size be proc get_type_size_bytes from Node with Node.get_node_output_type(node1 )
    Let node2_size be proc get_type_size_bytes from Node with Node.get_node_output_type(node2 )

    Let bandwidth_gbs be proc memory_get_float64 from Layout with cost_model, 0
    Let bandwidth_bs be bandwidth_gbs multiplied by 1000000000.0

    Let node1_size_float be proc int_to_float from Math with node1_size
    Let node2_size_float be proc int_to_float from Math with node2_size

    Let memory_time be (node1_size_float plus node2_size_float) divided by bandwidth_bs

    Note: Add launch overhead
    Let launch_overhead_us be proc memory_get_float64 from Layout with cost_model, 16
    Let launch_overhead_s be launch_overhead_us divided by 1000000.0
    Let launch_time be launch_overhead_s multiplied by 2.0

    Let total_time be compute_time plus memory_time plus launch_time

    Return total_time
End Process

Process called "compute_total_memory_traffic" that takes graph as Integer, node1 as Integer, node2 as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Compute total memory traffic for both nodes
    Let node1_size be proc get_type_size_bytes from Node with Node.get_node_output_type(node1 )
    Let node2_size be proc get_type_size_bytes from Node with Node.get_node_output_type(node2 )

    Note: Each node: read inputs + write output
    Note: Simplified: assume 2x data size
    Let total be (node1_size plus node2_size) multiplied by 2

    Return total
End Process

